<br>
Hinduism is generally considered to be the oldest religion still being practiced today. The texts they created are the Vedas, which were written around 1,500 B.C.E. (before common era). <br>
<br>
As far as oldest organized religion... Zoroastrianism. Scholars are not certain when the founding prophet Zarathustra actually lived. Some believe Zarathustra lived in the 6th century B.C.E., while others trace his writings to the 14th or 13th centuries B.C.E. <br>
<br>
Oddly enough, the two religions that dominate the world today are relative newcomers to the spiritual scene. Christianity began with the teachings of Jesus Christ around 30 C.E., and Islam started in 610 C.E. with the prophet Muhammad's revelation. <br>
<br>
Now...  do you want to equate superstition and religion into same thing.. then we have a whole new arena.<br>
<br>
Human cultural evolution is nromally broken into bands, tribes, kingdoms and empires.<br>
<br>
Bands.- Normally had no religious leader each person had &quot;power&quot; some more than others for specific means.<br>
<br>
Tribes.- had more definided labor distribution.. including the distribution of &quot;power&quot;. First religious leaders arise in these units(shamans).<br>
<br>
Kingdoms.- By the time a culture gets t this phase labor specialization is marked.  Including the building of houses of worship, temples and religious offices(high priests).<br>
<br>
Empires.- When empires arrive religious organizations can and do sometimes cross geopolitical lines.  This is due to a separation of religion and state in regards to some goals.<br>
<br>
